    "body": "After `PruneBlockIndexCandidates()` is called, the candidate set must include the current chain tip or a successor of it.\r\n\r\n`PruneBlockIndexCandidates()` removes candidates with less work than the active tip. However, because the tip itself is never added to `setBlockIndexCandidates` via `TryAddBlockIndexCandidate()`, it may be absent from the set. Prior to this patch, if all lower-work candidates were pruned and the tip was not present, `setBlockIndexCandidates` could become emptyâ€”violating an invariant relied upon by `FindMostWorkChain()`.\r\n\r\nThis patch ensures that `PruneBlockIndexCandidates()` explicitly reinserts the current tip after pruning, preserving that invariant.\r\n\r\nFixes #33129",
